            <div class="tutorialBox full">
                <h2 class="underline medium">High Altitude Balloon Overview</h2>
                <p>High Altitude Balloons are large latex balloons that are filled with either hydrogen or helium and carry small payloads up to around 100,000 ft.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/what-is-a-hab">What is a HAB?</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/supplies">Supplies List</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/regulations">Regulations</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="http://spaceacademy.co.za/balloon/regulations.html">South Africa: Regulations</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/safety">Safety</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/cost">Cost Breakdown</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="http://spaceacademy.co.za/balloon/cost_breakdown.html">South Africa: Cost Breakdown</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Camera</h2>
                <p>Mount a camera in your payload box to capture video to space and back!</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/camera">Camera Overview</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="http://spaceacademy.co.za/balloon/pi_camera.html">South Africa: Pi Camera</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/HABPhotographyHow-to-1.pdf" target="_blank">HAB Photography How To (PDF)</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox wider">
                <h2 class="underline medium">GPS Tracker and Radio</h2>
                <p>A GPS tracker shall be used that sends your geographic position to a webpage so that you can track down and recover your balloon.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/tracker">HAB Tracking Methods</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/tracker-products">Current Tracker Products</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/make-a-tracker">Build Your Own Tracker: Antenna Theory</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="http://spaceacademy.co.za/balloon/tracking_methods.html">South Africa: Tracking Methods</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Balloon</h2>
                <p>Balloons are typically purchased components that are sized depending on the payload size and desired altitude.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/balloon">Balloon Details</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="http://spaceacademy.co.za/balloon/balloons_parachutes.html">South Africa: Balloons and Parachutes</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Payload</h2>
                <p>An insulated payload box holds all of your  components like a camera, GPS tracker, radio and sensors.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/payload">Payload Details</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/power">Power</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Parachute</h2>
                <p>The parachute engages once the payload is in free fall and slows its descent to the ground.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/parachute">Parachute Details</a>
                </div>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="http://spaceacademy.co.za/balloon/balloons_parachutes.html">South Africa: Balloons and Parachutes</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Balloon Inflation and Gases</h2>
                <p>Balloons are typically inflated with helium and usually require an inflation tube.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/helium">Balloon Inflation and Gases details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox advanced">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Sensors</h2>
                <p>Not a requirement for beginning balloonist. Record temperature, pressure, and other atmospheric data data of the upper stratosphere using commercial sensors.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/sensor">Sensor Details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Radar Reflector</h2>
                <p>Radar reflectors are required so that planes can spot a balloon in the air.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/radar-reflector">Radar Reflector Details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Cord and Connectors</h2>
                <p>Tie all of your components together with a 25 lb tension rope.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/rope">Rope Details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tutorialBox advanced">
                <h2 class="underline medium">Flight Termination Unit</h2>
                <p>Not a requirement for beginning balloonists. This unit is designed to break the rope and release the payload at a specific time.</p>
                <div class="tutorial">
                    <a href="/flight-termination">Flight Termination Unit Details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
